[2] Cholera - Kenya (Coast Province)
Date: Wed, 27 Sep 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The Nation (Nairobi) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200609270076.html>

The number of people being treated for cholera at Vanga Health Centre
in Kwale District has risen to 15. 2 people have so far died of the
disease and most of the patients were children.
On Mon, 25 Sep 2006, the provincial medical officer of health, Dr
Anderson Kahindi, asked villagers during a tour of the area that
borders Tanzania to put chlorine water from wells. "We have
identified the source of the disease as the wells and have
chlorinated them," Dr Kahindi told the Nation by telephone.
By yesterday, 26 Sep 2006, 30 people from the area had been treated
and discharged.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
