[3] Cholera - Kenya (Coast Province)
Date: Mon, 25 Sep 2006
From: SK Sharif <sksharif@ikenya.com>

The Ministry of Health of Kenya has confirmed an outbreak of cholera
in Vanga Village in Kwale District in Kenya. The first case reported
on 17 Sep 2006 and by 25 Sep 2006 there were 45 reported cases. So
far there have been 2 deaths.
Vanga village is on the southern Coast of Kenya bordering Tanzania.
The area is cholera endemic with frequent outbreaks. The last
outbreak reported from the area was in 2004. The source of
contamination is thought to be water in shallow wells and the wells
have been contaminated by pit latrines which are very close to the well.
--
Dr S K Sharif
Ministry of Health, Kenya
<sksharif@ikenya.com>
[ProMED thanks Dr. Sharif for this report. A map of Kenya showing the
the Location of Kwale District in Coast Province can be found at:
<http://www.cnn.com/WORLD/africa/9911/04/kenya.roads/kenya.nairobi.kwale.jpg>
- Mod.LL]
